superccd2dng (1.4.4) stable; urgency=low

  * Add an R noise reduction slider in the Transition Settings group,
    using a combined luma + color bilateral filter with activity curve
    to suppress grain and chroma noise in the R pixel plane before
    the S+R merge
  * Add --r-luma-nr CLI flag for batch processing
  * Apply NR in parallel by horizontal bands with zero-copy optimization
    when both sliders are at 0

 -- Eduardo Anibarro <anibarro@example.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 23:00:00 +0200

superccd2dng (1.4.3) stable; urgency=low

  * Add a new Tone Mapping control group to the preview adjustments panel
    with Tone balance and Balance bias sliders, each backed by a numeric
    spin box for precise input
  * Add a two-stage tone-mapping curve that lifts shadows and compresses
    highlights while preserving midtone contrast via a local sigmoid
    contrast correction centred on the pivot
  * Add a Balance bias control that shifts the tone curve pivot so the
    user can favour shadow preservation or highlight preservation
  * Reorganize the preview adjustments panel into visual groups
    (Tone Mapping, Shadow Recovery, Color) with styled panel frames
    for a cleaner, more scannable layout
  * Improve the shadow recovery range control with a proportional
    smoothstep falloff that scales with the pivot point, so low range
    values have narrow transitions and high range values have wide
    transitions for a more natural look at all settings

 -- Eduardo Anibarro <anibarro@example.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 22:30:00 +0200

superccd2dng (1.4.2) stable; urgency=low

  * Add a new Exposure Tools window with Histogram and Waveform overlays
    for the live preview, each with All / RGB split / Luma visualization modes
  * Add a "Meter visible area only" toggle to scope histogram and waveform
    sampling to the sub-rect currently visible in the Preview window
  * Add a Transparency slider/spin box to the Waveform tab so the overlay
    can be dialed back over a busy preview
  * Retune the histogram and waveform visualizations for a cleaner look
    (tighter line weights, more readable color palette, consistent grid
    and axis decorations)
  * Use per-column peak normalization in the waveform so a single bright
    column does not dim every other column in the trace
  * Cache the source image and visible rect in the exposure tools so
    adjusting a slider does not force a full histogram + waveform
    recompute on every tick (especially noticeable on the Raspberry Pi)

 -- Eduardo Anibarro <anibarro@example.com>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 14:30:00 +0200

superccd2dng (1.4.1) stable; urgency=low

  * Add a Transition Curve graph widget that visualizes the live S->R merge
  * Make the Transition Settings group collapsible and persist its expanded state
  * Refine the merge slider mapping at the top of the S brightness range and add a dedicated MergeStartTest
  * Rework the DNG writer to emit a proper EXIF IFD and use the standard EXIF ISO speed ratings tag (34855)
  * Write DNG exposure times as true TIFF RATIONAL fractions and fix aperture, focal length, and ColorSpace handling
  * Share the macOS DNG metadata path with Windows so the EXIF IFD is populated on macOS exports
  * Parallelize the AMaZE preview demosaic and add an AmazeDemosaic test
  * Fix the AMaZE preview export size and clean up macOS build warnings
  * Update Raspberry Pi install instructions and refresh generated .deb packaging metadata

 -- Eduardo Anibarro <anibarro@example.com>  Fri, 03 Jul 2026 19:30:00 +0200

